ctrees.tidy <- ctrees %>%
  select(trunks, CommonName, Genus, species, TreeCondit, Location, diameter, BareRoot, TreeID) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(Genus)) %>% 
  filter(trunks == 1) %>% 
  # filter(Location == "Street Tree") %>% 
  select(TreeID, Genus, species, CommonName, diameter, Location) %>% 
  #remove genus abbrevs from species column
  mutate(species = str_remove(species, "\\w\\.\\s?")) %>% 
  mutate(species = ifelse(is.na(species), "sp.", str_to_lower(species))) %>% 
  #remove species name from genus column
  mutate(Genus = str_remove(Genus, " \\w+"))
factor(ctrees.tidy$Location) %>% levels()
 [1] "Back of Sidewalk" "Campus"           "Cemetery Tree"    "City Building"    "Former Tree"      "Golf Course"     
 [7] "Park Tree"        "Planting Strip"   "Public School"    "Street Tree"

Randomly sample some trees for a t-test question

rr streetmaples <- ctrees.tidy %>% filter(Location == Tree) %>% filter(Genus == ) parkmaples <- ctrees.tidy %>% filter(Location == Tree) %>% filter(Genus == ) spookymaples <- ctrees.tidy %>% filter(Location == Tree) %>% filter(Genus == ) maples <- bind_rows(sample_n(parkmaples, 20), sample_n(spookymaples, 20))

rr t.test(diameter ~ Location, data = maples)


    Welch Two Sample t-test

data:  diameter by Location
t = 1.8267, df = 30.474, p-value = 0.07755
alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
95 percent confidence interval:
 -0.8209631 14.8209631
sample estimates:

                      19.85                       12.85

Export maples data

rr maples %>% select(-species) %>% write_csv(here(7, , .csv))

Ginkgos

ginkgos <- ctrees.tidy %>% filter(Genus %in% c("Ginkgo", "Gingko")) %>% 
  filter(Location %in% c("Park Tree", "Street Tree")) %>% 
  group_by(Location) %>% 
  sample_n(15)
 
ggplot(ginkgos, aes(x = diameter)) + geom_histogram(bins = 5) + facet_wrap(~Location, scales = "free_x")
